# /io-report: Input-Output Economic Impact Assessment

Produces a quantitative economic impact assessment for an investment or jobs commitment in a specific sector and local area. Builds regional input-output tables, computes direct and indirect supply-chain multipliers via FLQ regionalization, applies additionality adjustments (deadweight, displacement, leakage), and estimates net impact on output, employment, and GVA.

Supports 391 UK local authorities and 88 Australian SA4 regions. Auto-detects country from location name and currency.

## Arguments

```
/io-report [investment description] [options]
```

**Examples:**
```
/io-report "GBP 10m in Manufacturing in Manchester"
/io-report "500 jobs in Construction in Glasgow"
/io-report "AUD 50m in Accommodation and food services, Melbourne"
/io-report "GBP 5m in Professional services, Leeds" --type2
/io-report ... --conservative
```

**Options:**
- `--type2` : Use Type II multipliers (include induced effects from household consumption). Default is Type I (direct + indirect only, HMT convention).
- `--conservative` : Apply higher additionality haircuts (30% deadweight, 40% displacement, 20% leakage) per HMT "conservative" guidance.
- `--optimistic` : Apply lower haircuts (10% / 15% / 5%).
- `--section <name>` : Emit only one sub-component. Options: `full` (default), `headline`, `inputs`, `multipliers`, `impact`, `additionality`, `sensitivity`, `limitations`. Combinable with commas.
- `--format <type>` : Output format(s). `markdown` (default, always generated), `xlsx`, `word`, `pptx`, `pdf`, or `all`.
- `--client "Name"` : Add "Prepared for" metadata.

