## Important rules

- **Regional IO is an approximation.** FLQ regionalization has known biases. State this in the Limitations section.
- **HMT additionality defaults** (20% / 25% / 10%) are the central case. Override with `--conservative` or `--optimistic` only with justification.
- **Type I is the default.** Type II multipliers are optional and only appropriate when induced effects are not already captured elsewhere.
- **Tax revenue estimates are indicative only.** They are not a formal fiscal impact assessment. Direct the reader to `/fiscal-briefing` for fiscal-grade work.
- **Honest about limitations.** Never claim IO impact figures as a definitive measure of regional benefit. Use them as a structured indication subject to additionality adjustments.
- **Em dashes**: never use em dashes. Use commas, colons, parentheses, or "and".

